{
    "name": "Giant Locust",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> temperate or warm deserts or plains<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, gang (3\u20138), or colony (5\u201320)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Leap (Ex)</b> A giant locust can take 10 on Acrobatics checks to jump even if distracted or in danger.<br/><br/><b>Spit (Ex)</b> A giant locust can spit a brown jet of acid and partially digested food up to 30 feet with no range increment.<br/><br/><b>Voracious (Ex)</b> A giant locust\u2019s bite attack deals double damage to creatures with the plant subtype and to objects made of paper, wood, or other plant materials."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Giant locusts have a hunger akin to their smaller cousins, but only rarely do they gather in the endless numbers of their tiny kin.<br/><br/>A mature giant locust measures just over 4 feet long and weighs 50 pounds."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>The mandibles of this enormous grasshopper churn and grind as it quests for food.</i>",
